      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>Old Testament  apocryphon of Jannes and Jambres, translated from Greek, existing in one known fragment, Schneider  ms. frag. 19.  The  translation  of Jannes and Jambresinto  Ge‘ez  took  place  at  some point between the late fourth and sixth centuries, the time frame in which specialists  agree  that  translational  activity  into  Ethiopic  directly  from Greek  transpired.
            </p>
         </abstract>
